    <text id="F0043T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Taggart answers his brother's question about the transfer policies for non-
                    commissioned officers.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Captain John Taggart, 9th Penn. Reserve Infantry</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-09-09">Monday Morning <abbr expan="September">Sept.</abbr>
                                9<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1861 </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear John, </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your <unclear>letter</unclear> of the 3<hi rend="super">d</hi> containing a paper
                    of <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> came to hand Saturday evening bearing an envelope "Not sent
                    forwarded" which accounts for its delay.</p>

                <p>I would write you a letter in answer, but we have everything packed up to go out
                    to "<hi rend="underline">Big Falls</hi>" on a seven days picket excursion. As I
                    may not have an opportunity of writing until my return you must not be uneasy<pb
                        n="2"/> if you do not hear from me.</p>

                <p>In relation to transfer A "Non Commissioned officer or soldier" may be
                    transferred from one Regiment to the other by Authority of the Commanding
                    General. Or a like transfer may be made from one Company to another in the same
                    Regiment by the Colonel subject to approval of the <abbr expan="Commanding"
                        cert="no">Com</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="General">Gen</abbr>. </p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>In a hurry Your Brother </salute>
                    <signed>Bob </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
